0.4.0 - 2013-12-17
  - Now works using Meteor 0.6.7 connection api, immediately detects most connection/disconnections
  - Api change, use Meteor.Presence.configure() to configure settings

0.3.0 - 2013-10-14
  - Added configurability to timeouts thanks @nathan-muir!

0.2.4 - 2013-08-18
  - Now works with Meteor 0.6.5

0.2.3 - 2013-08-08
  - Fixed problem on refresh, thanks @tlau!

0.2.2 - 2013-08-08
  - Check method arguments, thanks @Dsyko!

0.2.1 - 2013-07-23
  - fix a bug when the user times out (e.g. laptop sleep), thanks @dburles!

0.2.0
  - deal much better with hot-code-reload -- no more double presence.

0.1.2
  - stop using upsert which is not supported

0.1.1:
  - Improvements to on/offline tracking.

0.1.0:
 - moved over to a presence collection so we could track more than one presence per user and presences of non-logged in users
 - added an update() function to manually get presence happening
